name: blinddb
audience: public
description: >
  Interactive demonstration of client-side encryption architecture.
  The server stores opaque encrypted blobs — it cannot read, search,
  or analyze user data. Part of the privacy stack supporting
  The Ephemeral Internet thesis.

domains:
  - privacy
  - cryptography
  - client-side-encryption
  - demonstration

voice:
  tone: precise, privacy-first
  principles:
    - The server is structurally blind — not policy-blind, architecturally blind
    - Encryption happens before data leaves the client
    - Searchability without server-side decryption
  anti-patterns:
    - Server-side decryption for any reason
    - Treating privacy as a policy toggle rather than structural guarantee

standards:
  code_review:
    - No plaintext user data on the server side
    - Crypto operations use audited libraries

connects_to:
  - signet
  - tessera
  - hermesp2p
  - agent-safe
